---------------------------------------------------------------------------
- README file for the External Phy Device Manager (EPDM) 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
1) Description
   -----------
   EPDM provides common API interface for Broadcom External PHY drivers.
 
2) To Unpack
   --------- 
   tar -zxvf epdm.<x.y.z>.tgz 
 
3) EPDM usage
   ----------
    EPDM is not a PHY driver source, user cannot use EPDM package as standalone source. It always needs to be used with PHY driver source. 
 
4) Recommendation for EPDM usage
   -----------------------------
   - User needs to compile and create the epdm library with the required driver support turned on in the Makefile. 

    Example 1
    ---------
    To enable evora support, uncomment following defines in the Makefile, 
       CFLAGS += -DPLP_EVORA_SUPPORT
       CFLAGS += -DPLP_MACSEC_SUPPORT

    Example 2
    ---------
    Multiple chip support can be enabled by uncommenting the corresponding lines in the Makefile.
    CFLAGS += -DPLP_DINO_SUPPORT
    CFLAGS += -DPLP_EVORA_SUPPORT

   - For chips supporting MACSEC uncomment the line
     CFLAGS += -DPLP_MACSEC_SUPPORT

- To access EPDM APIs, user application needs to include epdm.h and epdm_sec.h(if security and MAC operation needed).
 
- Reference Makefile and example for EPDM usage is available in PHY driver source (path: <CHIP>.<Y>.<Z>\<CHIP>_reference_application)

- Please refer to EPDM html documentation for a list of APIs, their signatures and structures used. HTML documentation is located at $EPDM/doc/html/index.html 

5) Inline command for compiling reference application with EPDM
   ------------------------------------------------------------

   gcc ref_application.c  -I /epdm -I ./ -o ./ref_app_out -g -Wall -Werror -Wno-uninitialized -L. ./libftd2xx.*a -ldl -lrt -lpthread -Wl,-whole-archive ../build/libphymodepil.a /libepdm.a -Wl,-no-whole-archive -lm -DPLP_<CHIP>_SUPPORT -DPLP_MACSEC_SUPPORT

6) Using EPDM with multiple chip family drivers
   ---------------------------------------------
    If user intends to use an EPDM version that is different (and newer) than the one released with the PHY driver
    the following steps need to be followed to enable the PHY driver to use epdm common defines.
       Step 1: Uncomment and define EPDM_HOME based on your EPDM installation directory in make\config.mk file of the PHY driver
       Step 2: Compile the driver with TMP_PHYMOD_EPIL_CPPFLAGS += -DUSE_EPDM_COMMON_DEFINES in make\config.mk file

    Note: By default driver uses common defines that is available in the driver package.

